Package org.gvsig.remoteClient.sld.filterEncoding

Class Summary
FComparisonOperator Implements the main functionalities to parse a comparison operator of a Filter Encoding expression.
A comparison operator is used to form expressions that evaluate the mathematical comparison between two arguments.
FExpression Implements the main functionalities to parse an Filter Encoding expression
The expression element is an abstrac element which means that it does not really exist and its only purpose is to act as a placeholder for the elements and combinations of elements that can be used o form expressions.
Filter Implements the main class expresion where the parsing of a Filter Encoding expression starts
A filter is any valid predicate expression that can be formed using the elements defined in the Filter Encoding specification.
FilterFactory Implements a class that allows the user to create an XML document from an expression
FilterTags Tags for Filter Encoding
FilterUtils Useful methods which are used during the parse or the storage of a Filter Encoding expression
FIsBetweenOperator Implements the main functionalities to parse an PropertyIsBetween element of a Filter Encoding expression
The IsBetween property is defined as a compact way of encoding a range check
FIsLikeOperator Implements the main functionalities to parse an ProperyIsLike element of a Filter Encoding expression
The PropertyIsLike element is intended to encode a character string comparison operator with pattern matching.
FIsNullOperator Implements the main functionalities to parse a PropertyIsNull element of a Filter Encoding expression
The PropertyIsNull element encodes an operator that checks to see if the value of its content is NULL.
FLogicOperator Implements the main functionalities to parse a logical operator of a Filter Encoding expression
A logical operator can be used to combine one or more conditional expressions.
FLogicOperatorNot Implements the main functionalities to parse a logical negation operator of a Filter Encoding expression
The logical negation operator (NOT) reverses the logical value of an expression
